year 2015 marked the 45th Anniversary of perennial classic-rock favorite, America. Forty plus years later, these friends are still making music together, touring the world and thrilling audiences with their timeless sound. From \"Ventura Highway,\" \"Sister Golden Hair\" and \"Lonely People,\" to \"A Horse With No Name,\" \"Tin Man,\" and many more, America scored a string of chart hits that've never left classic radio. But in 2007, they released an impressive disc, \"Here and Now\", that paired them with indie artists like Ryan Adams and Ben Kweller. That led to a couple more albums, including 2015's \"Lost & Found\", with previously unreleased tracks, plus a greatest-hits box set. Still touring with original members Gerry Beckley and Dewey Bunnell, you can find America's star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame -- but where you really need to see them shine is onstage at the Saban Theatre in Beverly Hills.
